  "riddle": "1. Begin your journey in a green enclave within Australia's buzzing metropolis. There lies a locale by the tributary's name, known for its nature walks. Note where this park resides, mentioned in its sidebar.\n\n2. What might the sky whisper of a grand city down under? Measure how high above the sea the arching coat of arms of New South Wales stands.\n\n3. Within the embrace of the harbor city, sacred structures abound. Count these places of reflection that grace the landscape.\n\n4. Unite your findings by combining the altitude you unearthed with the sacred count from the prior quest.\n\n5. The very first mark you made in clue 1, consider its initial character. How does it rank if one sang the alphabet's tune?\n\n6. At the coordinates of a southern landmark, how far does the skyline rise from 33.86778 latitude?\n\n7. To conclude the quest, calculate the distance between the heights from clues 2 and 5, find the absolute, and wrap it with the clasp of the final digit of the decade.",
